Date: 4 Sep 2001 09:15:14 +0100
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@vet.gla.ac.uk>
Source: Yahoo, Tue 4 Sep 2001 [edited
<http://espanol.yahoo.com/noticias/010829/actualidad/notimex/qroo-acciones-dengue-999109800.html>

Prevalence of Dengue/DHF in Mexico So Far in 2001
-------------------------------------------------
The Subsecretario de Prevencion a la Salud, Roberto Tapia Conyer, said that
so far in 2001 totals of 590 cases of dengue fever and 63 of dengue
hemorrhagic fever (DHF) have been detected in the country.
The National Center for Epidemiological Surveillance (Centro Nacional de
Vigilancia Epidemiologica) reported a 3-fold increase in the annual
incidence of cases compared with last year.
Dengue was first detected in 1979, and in 1996 a total of 512 of [cases of
DHF were detected. From 1994 to 1999 a total of 39 deaths were reported in
Veracruz; no casualties were reported in 2000. So far [in 2001 the total
number of confirmed cases in the state is 237, of which 3 are DHF.
Disinfection [is being carried out in Chetumal, Cancun, Quintana Roo,
Ciudad del Carmen, and Campeche. A water testing program has also been
implemented.
--
Pablo Nart
